WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:52.552 --> 00:53.887
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:53.970 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES

00:58.975 --> 01:01.186
Ghosts don't exist.

01:01.269 --> 01:03.563
Every ghost denies it at first.

01:03.646 --> 01:05.857
Then prove that I'm a ghost.

01:05.940 --> 01:07.150
All right.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.320
Tell me who you are.

01:10.403 --> 01:12.489
Me? I'm…

01:14.783 --> 01:16.117
Who am I?

01:17.368 --> 01:20.497
It's okay. Most ghosts
show this kind of reaction.

01:21.247 --> 01:22.999
Maybe I lost my memory.

01:23.500 --> 01:25.335
Did I get into an accident or something?

01:25.418 --> 01:27.086
If it's simple memory loss,

01:28.087 --> 01:30.131
tell me why you're floating in mid-air.

01:30.215 --> 01:31.633
I'm floating in mid-air?

01:31.716 --> 01:32.717
What the heck?

01:33.510 --> 01:34.511
This can't be.

01:36.429 --> 01:38.306
Has another ghost come?

01:38.973 --> 01:40.558
Is he here?

01:41.643 --> 01:43.770
Who is it this time?

01:43.853 --> 01:45.730
It's a man in his thirties.

01:46.231 --> 01:47.732
He doesn't accept that he's dead.

01:48.775 --> 01:50.568
I'm not dead, I tell you!

01:50.652 --> 01:51.986
He's now in the second stage.

01:52.070 --> 01:53.196
Anger.

01:53.279 --> 01:55.115
-Oh, my.
-Let's say that I'm dead.

01:55.198 --> 01:57.075
Next, bargaining.

01:57.158 --> 01:59.869
Theoretically speaking,
spiritual beings are impossible.

01:59.953 --> 02:02.705
Wow, a theoretical approach?

02:03.206 --> 02:04.207
This is new.

02:04.999 --> 02:08.711
Listen. In the 1880s,
the British physicist, William Crookes,

02:08.795 --> 02:11.381
the Nobel Prize winner in Medicine,
Charles Richet,

02:11.464 --> 02:14.717
and the Great Inventor, Edison,
tried to prove the existence of the soul,

02:14.801 --> 02:16.761
but they all failed in the end!

02:18.221 --> 02:20.348
W-What is it?

02:20.431 --> 02:21.891
Is he upset?

02:21.975 --> 02:25.687
He seems too educated
to believe in ghosts.

02:26.646 --> 02:28.857
Ignorance is bliss sometimes.

02:30.400 --> 02:31.609
Too bad for him.

02:32.318 --> 02:34.821
Why don't we sit down
and give him some time?

02:36.656 --> 02:38.533
Are you people kidding me?

02:39.576 --> 02:42.579
Fine, I'll prove it then.

02:43.204 --> 02:44.372
What the…

02:45.498 --> 02:46.499
What's going on?

02:48.459 --> 02:49.544
What is this?

02:50.795 --> 02:55.049
Maybe we should take him home
and feed him something delicious.

02:55.133 --> 02:57.927
I hope he isn't a pork or coffee lover.

02:58.511 --> 03:00.555
That won't be good at all if he is.

03:02.765 --> 03:05.518
-Music.
-Right, music.

03:05.602 --> 03:07.020
What should I play?

03:08.187 --> 03:09.480
What would be a good choice?

03:17.447 --> 03:19.282
For a ghost to exist,

03:19.365 --> 03:22.535
it needs to have a physical entity
and create energy.

03:22.619 --> 03:24.662
But this is against
the basic laws of physics,

03:24.746 --> 03:27.040
the law of conservation
of mass and energy.

03:27.123 --> 03:28.124
One more thing.

03:38.468 --> 03:42.013
For a ghost to exist,
it needs to transcend time and space.

03:42.096 --> 03:45.266
This also is against
the basic laws of physics.

03:45.350 --> 03:46.351
In conclusion,

03:46.434 --> 03:50.813
no scientific evidence proves
the existence of ghosts…

04:00.907 --> 04:02.575
He seems to have majored in science.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.453
I…

04:05.536 --> 04:06.579
I found him.

04:11.209 --> 04:13.503
DR. JEON SANG-HO ON THE PODIUM
AS SCIENTIST OF THE YEAR

04:13.586 --> 04:15.255
INFORMATION
ON VICTIM JEON SANG-HO

04:15.338 --> 04:18.883
Jeon Sang-ho was the next leader
of the life sciences field in Korea.

04:20.260 --> 04:23.096
He was the Scientist of the Year
for three years in a row.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.975
He was outstanding enough
to be called a genius.

04:27.809 --> 04:29.394
KEY FIGURES
RELATED TO THE VICTIM

04:31.145 --> 04:32.230
Congratulations.

04:32.313 --> 04:35.400
<i>Chief Kim Tae-jun was fond of him</i>
<i>from the beginning.</i>

04:35.483 --> 04:36.484
7 YEARS AGO, YEAR 2018

04:36.567 --> 04:40.321
Say hello. This is Dr. Jeon Sang-ho.
He'll be joining our lab soon.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.657
And this is my daughter, Kim Su-jeong.

04:42.740 --> 04:43.741
Hello.

04:44.450 --> 04:45.618
Nice to meet you.

04:45.702 --> 04:47.996
I read your paper from last month.
It was impressive.

04:48.079 --> 04:50.957
EVEN ON HIS BIRTHDAY,
JEON SANG-HO PRESENTS NEW THEORY

04:53.751 --> 04:56.754
We've got his name and date of birth.

04:56.838 --> 05:00.300
He was 26 years old in 2018.

05:00.383 --> 05:02.302
He was born in 1992,
the Year of the Monkey.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.225
What's wrong?

05:09.976 --> 05:10.977
What is it?

05:13.521 --> 05:15.857
Take a deep breath.

05:16.441 --> 05:17.608
Excuse me?

05:19.152 --> 05:20.570
Inhale.

05:22.238 --> 05:23.323
Exhale.

05:24.490 --> 05:25.533
Wait.

05:25.616 --> 05:27.785
I'm sensitive to dust particles.

05:27.869 --> 05:30.204
And breathing too fast
will cause my cerebral blood flow--

05:30.288 --> 05:31.831
One more time.

05:38.504 --> 05:40.214
The moment I tell you

05:40.298 --> 05:42.467
your name and birthday,

05:42.967 --> 05:45.344
you'll regain all of your memories.

05:45.428 --> 05:47.930
If you're trying to hypnotize me,
it won't work.

05:48.014 --> 05:52.351
Hypnosis is a state of trance where
hyper-immersion distorts your perception.

05:52.435 --> 05:54.645
It, instead, reduces
the accuracy of your memory.

05:54.729 --> 05:56.189
In the field of science, it's very--

05:56.272 --> 05:58.274
Don't worry
even if you feel like throwing up.

05:58.357 --> 05:59.859
Ghosts can't throw up.

06:00.485 --> 06:01.778
All right, now.

06:01.861 --> 06:05.156
You were born on July 10, 1992.

06:05.865 --> 06:07.158
Your name is Jeon Sang-ho.

06:13.122 --> 06:16.751
JEON SANG-HO

07:18.855 --> 07:20.273
SCIENTIST OF THE YEAR
AWARD CEREMONY

07:20.356 --> 07:25.319
Chief Kim Tae-jun spared no expense
in supporting Jeon Sang-ho who was poor.

07:25.403 --> 07:29.073
<i>Jeon Sang-ho and Kim Su-jeong</i>
<i>quickly became close,</i>

07:29.157 --> 07:30.950
<i>having a shared interest in life sciences.</i>

07:33.536 --> 07:35.746
<i>After a year, they got married.</i>

07:35.830 --> 07:37.206
Congratulations on getting married!

07:37.874 --> 07:40.460
<i>Shortly after, they had a son.</i>

07:42.628 --> 07:45.506
<i>The successful husband and the wise wife.</i>

07:46.174 --> 07:51.137
<i>And with an adorable child, he had</i>
<i>all he needed to make a happy family.</i>

07:55.433 --> 07:56.601
<i>Until one day…</i>

07:58.936 --> 08:00.605
<i>Jeon Sang-ho went missing.</i>

08:11.616 --> 08:15.870
<i>His parents found it odd that they were</i>
<i>unable to reach him and called the police.</i>

08:15.953 --> 08:16.954
Come and check this.

08:18.623 --> 08:20.291
-This is blood, isn't it?
-Yes.

08:21.459 --> 08:23.753
<i>Bloodstains found in the grout lines</i>
<i>on the living room floor</i>

08:24.337 --> 08:26.297
<i>turned out to be Jeon Sang-ho's,</i>

08:26.881 --> 08:29.926
<i>and the missing person case</i>
<i>turned into a murder case.</i>

08:32.762 --> 08:34.972
I was out running that evening.

08:35.056 --> 08:36.307
Right over there…

08:46.192 --> 08:50.112
Based on her psychiatric records,

08:50.196 --> 08:53.991
the prosecution arrested Kim Su-jeong
on suspicion of murdering Jeon Sang-ho.

08:54.075 --> 08:56.869
There were no suspects other than her.

08:56.953 --> 08:59.747
Kim Su-jeong admitted
that they had an argument,

08:59.830 --> 09:02.708
but she claimed it was
no worse than any other lovers' quarrel.

09:03.292 --> 09:06.379
She also said she saw a psychiatrist
for minor postpartum depression.

09:06.462 --> 09:10.675
Besides that, his body wasn't found
and neither was the murder weapon.

09:10.758 --> 09:15.429
Most of all, no concrete evidence proved
that she murdered Jeon Sang-ho.

09:17.181 --> 09:20.935
After that, she was found not guilty,
but the prosecution appealed.

09:21.519 --> 09:25.773
It means they found something,
which we haven't figured out yet.

09:28.693 --> 09:29.860
What's your solution to this?

09:29.944 --> 09:34.073
Kim Su-jeong is the one who knows
what the prosecution has against her.

09:34.657 --> 09:36.075
I'll have to meet Kim Su-jeong.

09:37.326 --> 09:40.288
Are you feeling better now?

09:41.455 --> 09:42.456
Yes.

09:47.795 --> 09:49.547
I'm sorry to ask

09:50.631 --> 09:52.091
in this situation,

09:53.384 --> 09:55.177
but do you remember

09:56.554 --> 09:57.555
who killed you?

10:01.434 --> 10:03.603
The prosecution filed an appeal.

10:04.186 --> 10:06.480
That means they found something crucial,

10:06.564 --> 10:09.191
whether it be evidence or a witness.

10:10.818 --> 10:12.236
What do you think it is?

10:14.864 --> 10:19.910
All my conversations with you
will be confidential.

10:21.203 --> 10:22.913
So, please tell me honestly.

10:23.664 --> 10:26.542
Is the culprit your wife?

10:28.961 --> 10:30.129
I…

10:30.212 --> 10:31.297
I…

10:33.257 --> 10:35.051
did not kill my husband.

10:35.134 --> 10:36.719
…was murdered by my wife.

11:09.502 --> 11:12.213
You must be at ease,
being clueless and all.

11:14.048 --> 11:16.717
But I'm walking on thin ice.

11:18.677 --> 11:21.555
I'm not sure if I should stop I-rang.

11:23.391 --> 11:26.811
What if I leave him be
and something bad happens?

11:26.894 --> 11:28.604
I'm on pins and needles every day.

11:31.774 --> 11:36.529
It seems like I-rang is paying the price
for what you did.

11:38.280 --> 11:39.323
It's maddening.

11:42.576 --> 11:44.537
So, don't smile like that.

11:56.632 --> 11:59.260
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

12:00.428 --> 12:04.056
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

12:05.808 --> 12:07.435
Goodness, there we go.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.107
They're staying at her parents'.

12:14.442 --> 12:15.443
Figures.

12:15.526 --> 12:19.321
It wouldn't be easy to stay
at the murder location.

12:23.534 --> 12:24.577
U-ju…

12:26.245 --> 12:29.623
I get that you're heartbroken,
but don't cry.

12:30.124 --> 12:33.002
You have to be strong at a time like this.

12:33.085 --> 12:34.211
I apologize.

12:34.295 --> 12:36.088
You have nothing to apologize for.

12:39.258 --> 12:42.553
Why do all my ghost clients
have to be so good-natured?

12:46.348 --> 12:48.601
Geez, I hate this.

12:48.684 --> 12:49.894
Thank you.

12:58.527 --> 13:01.530
RESTRICTED AREA - POLICE LINE
UNDER INVESTIGATION

13:22.718 --> 13:26.764
Are you going to be okay?
This is where you got killed.

13:27.348 --> 13:29.099
Objects, locations,
smells, and such things

13:29.767 --> 13:31.977
can be of great help
in regaining one's memory.

13:32.645 --> 13:34.939
I want to remember anything I can.

14:11.225 --> 14:14.103
What did you do
after you came home from work that day?

14:16.272 --> 14:19.400
I had an argument with Su-jeong.

14:20.317 --> 14:21.318
Why?

14:24.405 --> 14:26.240
Why aren't the results out yet?

14:26.907 --> 14:28.367
I'm tired. Let's talk tomorrow.

14:29.368 --> 14:31.704
Are you taking your time
because it's none of your business?

14:31.787 --> 14:33.080
What?

14:33.664 --> 14:34.915
This isn't my business?

14:35.416 --> 14:37.293
Are you saying I'm not your family?

14:39.920 --> 14:41.213
I'm done.

14:41.964 --> 14:43.883
-What?
-I quit.

14:44.466 --> 14:46.302
You don't even consider me as family.

14:47.428 --> 14:49.263
It's foolish
to be the only one giving their all.

14:49.346 --> 14:50.347
Honey.

14:52.641 --> 14:55.644
Are you really trying to kill me?

14:55.728 --> 14:57.521
I don't care if you die or not!

14:58.606 --> 15:00.566
I'm sick and tired of this.

15:04.403 --> 15:05.404
It was just

15:06.447 --> 15:07.698
a common lovers' quarrel.

15:08.324 --> 15:09.325
And then?

15:30.387 --> 15:32.264
<i>Su-jeong and U-ju seemed to be asleep.</i>

15:33.599 --> 15:34.725
<i>So, I went to wash up.</i>

15:40.147 --> 15:43.734
Are you sure it was only you,
your wife, and your child in the house?

15:45.527 --> 15:46.570
Yes.

15:48.405 --> 15:50.115
What else do you remember?

15:51.283 --> 15:52.493
Well…

15:56.288 --> 15:57.998
I did see something.

15:59.416 --> 16:02.711
But the mirror was so foggy…

16:05.339 --> 16:06.423
I couldn't see clearly.

16:11.428 --> 16:12.638
I'm not sure.

16:15.265 --> 16:16.266
I don't know…

16:20.312 --> 16:22.022
<i>This is the info on Shin I-rang, sir.</i>

16:22.106 --> 16:23.482
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

16:23.565 --> 16:26.235
ADDRESS:
OKCHEON BUILDING, SEOCHO

16:26.318 --> 16:27.987
His office is in Seocho-dong?

16:29.196 --> 16:30.656
He's way out of his league.

16:31.323 --> 16:35.619
And we have a criminal trial scheduled
for the Glory girl group case.

16:42.292 --> 16:43.794
PLAINTIFF'S LEGAL REP:
SHIN I-RANG

16:43.877 --> 16:45.295
DEFENDANT: MOON JU-HYEON (EMMA)

16:47.339 --> 16:48.424
Shin I-rang?

16:48.507 --> 16:50.926
He's the legal representative
of the victim Kim Su-a.

16:53.762 --> 16:54.930
What's with this punk?

17:04.481 --> 17:06.650
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE - APPEAL

17:08.277 --> 17:10.362
ERROR OF FACT
ERROR OF LAW - NEW EVIDENCE

17:11.739 --> 17:13.657
What on earth did they find?

17:38.390 --> 17:40.893
DAD

18:01.330 --> 18:02.372
Hello?

18:02.456 --> 18:04.625
<i>Hey, she picked up.</i>
<i>Come on and take the phone.</i>

18:04.708 --> 18:06.293
<i>Really?</i>

18:06.376 --> 18:07.377
Dad?

18:07.461 --> 18:09.129
<i>Talk to her before she hangs up.</i>

18:09.213 --> 18:11.256
<i>Hello?</i>

18:11.340 --> 18:12.716
<i>Na-hyun.</i>

18:13.550 --> 18:16.595
<i>N-Na-hyun, it's Dad.</i>

18:16.678 --> 18:17.679
Yes, I know.

18:18.222 --> 18:19.264
Are you having a drink?

18:19.348 --> 18:25.062
Yes, I met up with Chan-u today
who I haven't seen in a long time.

18:25.145 --> 18:27.106
We were having a drink together

18:27.189 --> 18:30.192
when I was suddenly thought of you.

18:30.859 --> 18:33.695
Mom must be waiting.
Stop drinking and go home.

18:33.779 --> 18:36.782
<i>Na-hyun, make time for your dad.</i>

18:37.491 --> 18:39.660
Your dad is practically pining here.

18:39.743 --> 18:41.578
Don't be ridiculous.

18:41.662 --> 18:43.413
Na-hyun is extremely busy.

18:43.497 --> 18:45.749
She's not just any attorney.

18:45.833 --> 18:48.293
She's a partner attorney at Taebaek.

18:48.377 --> 18:49.878
<i>Oh, come on.</i>

18:49.962 --> 18:53.298
<i>Stop with the act. You were whining</i>
<i>about how much you missed her just now.</i>

18:53.382 --> 18:54.591
Be quiet.

18:54.675 --> 18:56.802
Hello? Na-hyun.

18:56.885 --> 18:58.387
Dad, I have to work.

18:58.470 --> 19:00.514
<i>I see. I'm sorry to disturb.</i>
<i>I'll let you work.</i>

19:00.597 --> 19:04.226
Yeah, I'll go home now. Let's hang up.

19:04.309 --> 19:05.477
Dad.

19:05.561 --> 19:07.563
<i>Yes? What is it, Na-hyun?</i>

19:09.106 --> 19:10.482
No, nothing.

19:10.566 --> 19:11.733
What?

19:11.817 --> 19:13.193
Well, okay.

19:13.819 --> 19:15.612
Let's hang up.

19:15.696 --> 19:18.574
I was about to head home anyway.

19:18.657 --> 19:20.075
Hanging up now.

19:26.665 --> 19:28.709
Be careful on your way home.

19:51.899 --> 19:52.941
Geez, you startled me.

19:53.567 --> 19:55.068
What are you doing?

19:55.152 --> 19:58.488
I'm sorry, but I can't sleep
when I'm curious about something.

19:58.572 --> 20:00.782
Ghosts don't sleep.

20:02.910 --> 20:04.828
Have you forgotten what the contract says?

20:04.912 --> 20:07.080
"A ghost client does not invade
the attorney's privacy."

20:07.164 --> 20:10.709
Sleep is my absolute privacy.

20:10.792 --> 20:11.793
Right.

20:13.128 --> 20:16.381
Fine. I'm awake anyway.

20:16.465 --> 20:18.717
Ask me your question.

20:21.345 --> 20:24.139
What happened
to all your former ghost clients?

20:25.307 --> 20:27.267
Their resentment was lifted.

20:27.351 --> 20:29.978
A child was set free
from her sense of guilt.

20:30.062 --> 20:32.064
A family reunited too.

20:32.648 --> 20:35.192
-And then?
-They went to a better place.

20:36.276 --> 20:38.487
Don't worry, Sang-ho.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.530
I'll make Kim Su-jeong pay the price

20:40.614 --> 20:42.783
and help you pass on.

20:44.409 --> 20:45.452
I don't want you to.

20:46.370 --> 20:47.829
What do you mean?

20:48.413 --> 20:50.249
Make Su-jeong pay the price.

20:51.875 --> 20:52.876
What?

20:54.127 --> 20:55.545
Why not?

20:55.629 --> 20:58.382
You had a bright future,
and she killed you.

20:59.007 --> 21:00.550
Even if she gets punished,

21:01.426 --> 21:03.387
I won't come back to life.

21:06.306 --> 21:08.058
You're right, but--

21:08.141 --> 21:09.142
I…

21:09.851 --> 21:11.603
get why she did it.

21:13.230 --> 21:15.732
She must've dreamed
of a happy married life

21:16.233 --> 21:18.235
with a husband who had the same goals.

21:18.860 --> 21:23.073
But I couldn't make her happy.

21:25.534 --> 21:26.952
Ouch.

21:31.248 --> 21:34.793
<i>I was always preoccupied with research.</i>

21:37.212 --> 21:40.465
<i>It was the same even after U-ju was born.</i>

21:45.470 --> 21:49.349
<i>I was afraid of dropping him</i>
<i>or hurting him.</i>

21:54.146 --> 21:55.147
Su-jeong.

21:55.230 --> 21:58.692
Goodness. Why are you
just staring at the baby?

21:58.775 --> 22:01.069
<i>I couldn't bring myself to touch him</i>

22:01.153 --> 22:04.239
<i>in case he got hurt because of me.</i>

22:05.615 --> 22:09.911
She was struggling just as much
with her first experience as a parent.

22:10.620 --> 22:15.334
But all I did was calculate and hide
instead of following my heart.

22:17.044 --> 22:20.964
She must've thought
I was frustrating and pathetic.

22:21.757 --> 22:23.717
There, there.

22:23.800 --> 22:26.094
Here you go. Have just one spoonful.

22:26.178 --> 22:29.765
U-ju, let's eat. Have your food.

22:29.848 --> 22:30.849
I'm off to work.

22:30.932 --> 22:34.686
<i>It's an excuse… to say I didn't know how.</i>

22:36.438 --> 22:38.482
I ruined her life.

22:40.525 --> 22:42.110
Su-jeong was so depressed

22:43.278 --> 22:44.738
that she even tried to kill herself.

22:48.617 --> 22:52.746
<i>I'm mostly to blame</i>
<i>for her postpartum depression.</i>

22:54.706 --> 22:55.707
Su-jeong.

22:56.374 --> 22:58.168
<i>If she had died back then…</i>

22:58.251 --> 23:00.170
-Su-jeong.
-<i>…I would've been the murderer.</i>

23:00.253 --> 23:02.506
What's going on? Su-jeong.

23:02.589 --> 23:04.883
-<i>I brought it upon her.</i>
-Su-jeong.

23:05.801 --> 23:08.303
-<i>I can't possibly blame her.</i>
-Su-jeong!

23:08.887 --> 23:10.222
That's really hard to believe.

23:10.305 --> 23:11.348
Anyway,

23:12.349 --> 23:14.851
at least for U-ju,

23:15.894 --> 23:18.021
I want Su-jeong to be found not guilty.

23:18.605 --> 23:21.024
Sang-ho. His dad is dead.

23:21.525 --> 23:23.527
If his mom goes to prison…

23:25.946 --> 23:28.073
I would feel so bad for U-ju.

23:31.827 --> 23:34.579
I couldn't be a good dad
while I was alive,

23:35.664 --> 23:38.291
but I want to be one now
even if it's late.

23:39.084 --> 23:40.293
For that to happen,

23:42.087 --> 23:43.964
we shouldn't take his mom away from him.

23:46.258 --> 23:48.051
Even if she's the one who murdered you?

23:52.180 --> 23:54.808
She's warm and sweet at heart.

23:55.934 --> 23:57.561
Now that I'm gone,

23:58.645 --> 24:01.189
she'll go back to how she used to be.

24:02.482 --> 24:05.235
Then, U-ju will be raised well.

24:12.659 --> 24:14.536
So, there are fathers like you after all.

24:16.663 --> 24:18.999
Others have fathers who don't give a damn

24:20.208 --> 24:21.877
about his child or family.

24:23.587 --> 24:24.713
What?

24:25.714 --> 24:26.756
I'm talking about my dad.

24:27.841 --> 24:30.719
He did whatever he wanted
in his carefree life

24:31.720 --> 24:34.306
until he died,
leaving the mess for us to clean up.

24:36.850 --> 24:38.310
Compared to him,

24:39.769 --> 24:41.563
you're an admirable dad.

24:42.939 --> 24:43.940
I'm sorry.

24:44.566 --> 24:45.650
Don't be.

24:47.360 --> 24:50.739
Anyway, tomorrow is the appellate trial.

24:50.822 --> 24:53.408
Let's wait and see
how the result turns out.

24:53.491 --> 24:54.492
Okay?

24:55.493 --> 24:56.494
Okay.

24:59.873 --> 25:01.875
Why is it so bright, though?

25:04.920 --> 25:06.838
The sun came up.

25:08.506 --> 25:09.716
I'm sorry.

25:09.799 --> 25:11.134
Stop with the apologies!

25:30.487 --> 25:32.447
COURTHOUSE

25:34.199 --> 25:35.408
Is Sang-ho here?

25:36.034 --> 25:40.080
No, I told him to wait
in case he possessed me.

25:40.163 --> 25:41.998
I see. Good job.

25:43.541 --> 25:44.709
You seem tired.

25:46.086 --> 25:47.087
That's Attorney Han.

25:48.088 --> 25:50.465
I'll be inside. Take your time.

26:00.058 --> 26:01.059
What was that?

26:01.142 --> 26:02.602
Well…

26:03.186 --> 26:04.437
I'm glad to see you.

26:05.021 --> 26:06.398
So, you pulled my hair?

26:06.481 --> 26:09.150
Pulling hair can be a way of expression.

26:11.027 --> 26:13.196
What brings you here, by the way?

26:13.280 --> 26:15.865
An attorney comes to the courthouse
for obvious reasons.

26:17.242 --> 26:18.660
COURT 401 ENTRANCE

26:18.743 --> 26:21.871
Don't tell me Kim Su-jeong is your client.

26:22.455 --> 26:24.374
That's none of your business.

26:25.500 --> 26:26.543
Wait.

26:28.420 --> 26:29.421
What now?

26:32.799 --> 26:33.842
Your nose.

26:34.968 --> 26:36.094
It's bleeding.

26:42.642 --> 26:46.104
-Why do I keep having a nosebleed?
-Rest when you can.

26:47.731 --> 26:49.357
Thanks for the advice.

26:49.983 --> 26:53.820
And don't work too hard on this case.

26:54.988 --> 26:57.532
The truth is bound to be revealed.

26:59.200 --> 27:00.243
What does that mean?

27:00.327 --> 27:04.456
Kim Su-jeong murdered her husband
brutally in the bathroom.

27:05.665 --> 27:08.209
Her denial is a lie.

27:08.877 --> 27:09.919
How do you know?

27:11.379 --> 27:13.214
I briefly told you the other day.

27:16.426 --> 27:17.635
A ghost told me.

27:20.930 --> 27:22.223
Let me ask you a favor.

27:23.641 --> 27:26.061
If you see me again,
pretend you don't know me.

27:27.437 --> 27:30.023
We aren't close enough
to exchange happy greetings, you know.

27:31.775 --> 27:32.859
Oh, one more thing.

27:33.526 --> 27:36.988
No one knows where or how Mr. Jeon died.

27:55.715 --> 27:57.092
I-rang, over here.

28:03.807 --> 28:05.475
Why do you have that thing?

28:06.059 --> 28:07.060
Well…

28:11.898 --> 28:12.899
What the heck?

28:13.483 --> 28:16.194
Attorney Han is the defense counsel?

28:17.529 --> 28:18.530
Yes.

28:22.158 --> 28:24.786
Why the long face? Did she tell you off?

28:28.289 --> 28:30.834
She wants me to act like I don't know her.

28:31.835 --> 28:33.211
Are you upset?

28:34.087 --> 28:36.548
I'm just a little sad.

28:53.022 --> 28:54.441
All rise.

29:04.868 --> 29:06.286
Please be seated.

29:08.830 --> 29:10.415
Let the trial commence.

29:10.498 --> 29:14.419
Case 2025-Noh-1361775,
Defendant Kim Su-jeong.

29:14.502 --> 29:16.588
DEFENSE TABLE

29:16.671 --> 29:17.672
Yes.

29:18.465 --> 29:22.886
During the first instance of this case,
Defendant Kim Su-jeong was acquitted

29:22.969 --> 29:26.139
as no evidence was provided
that Jeon Sang-ho was murdered

29:26.222 --> 29:29.642
and the defendant didn't have
the motive to murder him

29:29.726 --> 29:32.645
along with the lack of evidence
that the defendant murdered him.

29:33.688 --> 29:35.440
But after the first verdict,

29:35.523 --> 29:40.361
evidence has been found to prove
that Jeon Sang-ho was murdered

29:40.445 --> 29:42.697
and that the defendant murdered him.

29:42.781 --> 29:46.367
Thus, I set forth
that Defendant Kim Su-jeong is guilty.

29:47.494 --> 29:49.829
Please take a look
at evidence exhibits one and two.

29:54.626 --> 29:55.710
A shower curtain?

29:57.921 --> 29:59.756
I said it was the bathroom.

29:59.839 --> 30:03.218
These two exhibits were found
at the incineration site on the outskirts

30:03.301 --> 30:06.429
of the defendant's residential complex
after the first instance.

30:07.013 --> 30:09.808
The carpet and shower curtain
weren't destroyed by fire

30:09.891 --> 30:11.851
as they were highly noncombustible.

30:11.935 --> 30:15.522
And the blood analysis result
confirmed it to be the victim's blood.

30:16.940 --> 30:19.275
The murder took place in the bathroom.

30:19.359 --> 30:21.236
The body was moved to the living room,

30:21.319 --> 30:23.446
wrapped in the carpet, then moved outside.

30:23.530 --> 30:25.114
…DNA MATCH
WITH THAT OF JEON SANG-HO…

30:25.949 --> 30:27.909
It really was the bathroom?

30:27.992 --> 30:29.494
She should've believed me.

30:30.912 --> 30:32.497
Based on the forensic analysis results,

30:32.580 --> 30:35.416
more than two liters of blood
was absorbed by the carpet,

30:35.500 --> 30:38.211
and Jeon Sang-ho was assumed
to be already dead by then.

30:39.462 --> 30:40.880
He really died?

30:40.964 --> 30:44.968
Your Honor, the prosecution's claim
is all an assumption.

30:45.844 --> 30:47.637
I respect the defense counsel's opinion.

30:48.555 --> 30:51.015
Thus, I'd like
to present additional evidence

30:51.099 --> 30:53.434
that proves Jeon Sang-ho was murdered.

30:53.518 --> 30:54.686
BLOODSTAIN PATTERN ANALYSIS

30:58.064 --> 30:59.774
<i>We conducted a blood pattern analysis</i>

30:59.858 --> 31:02.402
<i>after installing a shower curtain</i>
<i>at the assumed place of murder.</i>

31:03.069 --> 31:06.364
The area of origin
was determined to be very high

31:06.447 --> 31:09.742
with the expiration pattern
to be very small and round.

31:09.826 --> 31:11.244
Based on this analysis,

31:11.327 --> 31:15.039
I contend that Defendant Kim Su-jeong
has an accomplice.

31:24.841 --> 31:26.050
Silence.

31:28.303 --> 31:31.180
Let us hear the prosecution's
legal grounds in more detail.

31:32.557 --> 31:37.061
The area of origin is
higher than 170 cm from the floor,

31:37.145 --> 31:40.899
which assumes that the culprit is
around 180 to 185 cm tall.

31:40.982 --> 31:44.527
The expiration pattern is small and round
with a diameter of less than 3 mm,

31:44.611 --> 31:48.781
which assumes that the act was done
with a quick and powerful force.

31:48.865 --> 31:49.866
This isn't good.

31:50.700 --> 31:55.121
Thus, I've concluded
that the defendant has an accomplice.

31:55.204 --> 31:56.623
That's not true.

31:58.958 --> 32:00.585
Let me ask you, Ms. Kim.

32:01.252 --> 32:02.545
Who is your accomplice?

32:03.630 --> 32:06.716
I object to the evidence
submitted by the prosecution.

32:06.799 --> 32:09.469
The evidence means there's a culprit.

32:09.552 --> 32:11.387
It doesn't indicate the defendant as one.

32:11.471 --> 32:15.224
The only suspect at the moment
is Kim Su-jeong who was in the house.

32:15.308 --> 32:18.144
But she couldn't have done it alone,

32:18.227 --> 32:20.104
so I contend that she has an accomplice.

32:20.188 --> 32:23.066
The prosecution's additional evidence
rather--

32:23.149 --> 32:24.150
I…

32:25.401 --> 32:27.403
I killed my husband.

32:31.240 --> 32:32.450
Ms. Kim, sit down.

32:32.533 --> 32:33.534
I…

32:34.202 --> 32:35.703
I lied.

32:36.996 --> 32:39.999
I did it alone. I killed my husband alone.

32:40.083 --> 32:43.711
The bloodstain was high up because
I was on a step stool when I attacked him.

32:44.379 --> 32:46.047
A kids' step stool.

32:46.130 --> 32:47.131
You murderer!

32:47.799 --> 32:49.968
-You think murder is a joke?
-How could you kill my son?

32:50.051 --> 32:51.177
How dare you!

33:02.647 --> 33:04.190
What's gotten into you?

33:07.568 --> 33:10.113
Why did you make that confession?

33:11.572 --> 33:13.574
It's the truth.

33:13.658 --> 33:15.618
You're protecting your accomplice,
aren't you?

33:19.038 --> 33:20.164
Who is it?

33:30.425 --> 33:33.344
Think of your child, Ms. Kim.

33:35.221 --> 33:36.806
You're a mom.

33:37.890 --> 33:40.018
Think only of your child and tell me.

33:41.227 --> 33:45.189
We need to prove
that you didn't murder your husband

33:45.773 --> 33:47.191
for you to go back to your child.

33:50.153 --> 33:51.571
Who is the accomplice?

33:54.907 --> 33:56.117
The accomplice…

34:04.876 --> 34:06.169
I don't have an accomplice.

34:18.765 --> 34:19.891
Who are you?

34:22.393 --> 34:23.561
Let's have a seat, shall we?

34:32.695 --> 34:34.947
I'm Yang Do-kyung,
the managing partner of Taebaek.

34:35.031 --> 34:37.033
MANAGING PARTNER YANG DO-KYUNG

34:38.367 --> 34:40.203
I have a few questions for you.

34:40.828 --> 34:44.999
Do you remember the man who was with you
when you got arrested?

34:45.083 --> 34:46.959
Damn right, I do.

34:48.544 --> 34:49.587
That damn lunatic.

34:51.798 --> 34:54.467
Will you tell me
what exactly happened that day?

34:55.051 --> 34:58.346
What happened and why you ended up
confessing unnecessarily--

34:58.429 --> 34:59.555
Damn it!

34:59.639 --> 35:00.932
Again?

35:01.015 --> 35:02.517
Just the thought of it pisses me off.

35:09.816 --> 35:11.567
You better tell me

35:11.651 --> 35:13.736
if you don't want
to rot in prison for 20 years.

35:15.571 --> 35:16.572
Twenty years?

35:16.656 --> 35:20.451
You'll be back outside
after all your good years are gone.

35:25.456 --> 35:26.833
Did that man perhaps

35:27.875 --> 35:29.252
behave unusually?

35:30.670 --> 35:31.796
How did you know?

35:32.672 --> 35:35.508
That man acted like Su-a.

35:37.135 --> 35:42.974
Actually, he spoke and acted like Su-a.

35:43.057 --> 35:44.767
He wasn't just like Su-a.

35:45.893 --> 35:47.186
He was Su-a himself.

35:53.609 --> 35:54.777
Ms. Kim.

35:55.361 --> 35:58.239
Could you find me
where Attorney Shin I-rang's office is?

36:11.878 --> 36:13.296
<i>It was Lee Gang-pung.</i>

36:14.338 --> 36:16.966
My underling back in the Oseong Gang,

36:18.134 --> 36:19.343
Lee Gang-pung.

36:19.427 --> 36:21.637
That man acted like Su-a.

36:28.436 --> 36:29.437
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

36:29.520 --> 36:31.189
ADDRESS:
OKCHEON BUILDING, SEOCHO

36:36.068 --> 36:37.737
SEARCH

36:40.323 --> 36:43.159
OKCHEON BUILDING

36:47.163 --> 36:48.456
A shaman's house?

36:48.539 --> 36:51.125
MALE SHAMAN

36:51.209 --> 36:54.754
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

36:54.837 --> 36:56.339
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

37:02.470 --> 37:04.013
That Kim Su-jeong…

37:04.639 --> 37:07.350
She seems to have confessed
to protect her accomplice, hasn't she?

37:08.309 --> 37:09.310
Yes.

37:09.894 --> 37:12.813
Goodness, Sang-ho might go crazy
if he hears this.

37:12.897 --> 37:13.940
-Bong-su.
-What?

37:14.023 --> 37:15.900
We must keep it from him.

37:15.983 --> 37:17.860
It's bad enough that he was murdered.

37:18.736 --> 37:21.739
If he hears that
the culprit is another man, not his wife,

37:21.822 --> 37:23.074
he'll go dark for sure.

37:23.157 --> 37:26.244
Of course, he won't be able to tolerate it
no matter how kind he may be.

37:26.911 --> 37:28.246
What will you do, then?

37:28.329 --> 37:30.539
We can't catch the culprit
with the truth hidden.

37:30.623 --> 37:33.960
And I have to go to work now.
Will you be okay alone?

37:34.752 --> 37:37.338
I'll try to find a way somehow.

37:37.421 --> 37:41.217
A way to catch the culprit
without provoking Sang-ho.

37:44.387 --> 37:45.638
Anyway,

37:46.430 --> 37:48.140
I wonder who visited the shaman.

37:49.850 --> 37:51.686
Maybe his parents did.

37:51.769 --> 37:53.646
In hopes of finding their son's body.

37:55.147 --> 37:56.857
That must be it.

37:56.941 --> 38:01.112
In the SBS drama, <i>Showboating Detective</i>,
which I played a part in,

38:01.195 --> 38:04.407
parents resort to all kinds of means
to find their child's body.

38:04.490 --> 38:08.995
And when the body is found, it has
tons of clues about the perpetrator.

38:13.207 --> 38:14.208
-Bong-su.
-What?

38:14.292 --> 38:15.293
That's it.

38:15.918 --> 38:18.671
A way to catch the culprit
without Sang-ho finding out.

38:26.887 --> 38:28.431
How did it go?

38:31.726 --> 38:33.144
There was nothing much.

38:34.395 --> 38:38.607
Then why was the case retried?

38:38.691 --> 38:40.693
The prosecution appealed.

38:41.319 --> 38:44.322
Your parents must've wanted it.

38:46.657 --> 38:49.535
They asked Kim Su-jeong to tell them
at least where your body was hidden,

38:49.618 --> 38:52.413
but she remained silent until the end.

38:53.539 --> 38:57.752
They probably visited the shaman
to find your body.

38:58.544 --> 39:00.087
Since your body is still missing,

39:01.213 --> 39:03.174
they must be devastated.

39:03.758 --> 39:05.217
Finding my body…

39:06.761 --> 39:07.762
won't change anything.

39:09.680 --> 39:13.934
In some cases,
seeing is the only way to move on.

39:19.231 --> 39:24.320
Perpetrators usually abandon the body
in a place familiar to them.

39:25.029 --> 39:28.866
A place familiar enough for Kim Su-jeong
to abandon a body.

39:28.949 --> 39:30.659
Does anywhere ring a bell?

39:30.743 --> 39:34.872
The places she'd go are home,
her parents' house,

39:35.915 --> 39:37.416
and the lab.

39:40.419 --> 39:42.963
-Oh, right.
-What is it?

39:43.047 --> 39:46.342
Right next to the lab is a potter's field.

39:47.843 --> 39:49.553
<i>It's a small hill,</i>

39:49.637 --> 39:53.516
<i>but no one goes there</i>
<i>because rumors say it's haunted.</i>

39:53.599 --> 39:56.143
Su-jeong and I didn't believe in ghosts,

39:56.852 --> 39:59.146
and it was a nice place to be alone,
so we often went there.

40:01.565 --> 40:04.193
It's perfect for hiding a body.

40:06.195 --> 40:07.196
Let's go right away.

40:14.495 --> 40:15.579
Attorney Han?

40:15.663 --> 40:16.831
How did you know?

40:16.914 --> 40:18.165
Excuse me?

40:21.168 --> 40:23.504
How did you know
that the place of murder was the bathroom?

40:25.673 --> 40:27.049
You won't believe me.

40:34.515 --> 40:36.434
That's right. A ghost told me.

40:40.438 --> 40:41.981
-Then prove it to me.
-Come on.

40:42.565 --> 40:45.109
How am I supposed to prove
what scientists can't?

40:45.693 --> 40:48.404
In the movies,
ghosts lift chairs and break windows.

40:49.029 --> 40:50.239
I won't ask for chair-lifting.

40:52.741 --> 40:53.909
Tell him to lift that.

40:56.620 --> 40:57.621
He can't.

40:57.705 --> 40:59.874
Then tell him to say something to me.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.418
Who is this woman?

41:03.711 --> 41:06.005
Ghosts who visit me
aren't capable of doing such stuff.

41:06.714 --> 41:09.216
They can neither hold nor move things.

41:09.300 --> 41:10.801
I'm the only one who can hear them.

41:10.885 --> 41:12.511
So you have no way to prove it.

41:13.429 --> 41:15.890
Then how am I supposed to see
if you're not talking nonsense?

41:20.811 --> 41:21.812
I have proof.

41:24.732 --> 41:25.733
Look.

41:26.484 --> 41:28.819
Sang-ho wrote this when he possessed me.

41:35.242 --> 41:36.243
Possessed?

41:38.412 --> 41:41.874
You have no intention
of telling me the truth.

41:41.957 --> 41:44.293
Check the handwriting
if you can't believe me.

41:44.376 --> 41:45.377
Ask Sang-ho's family…

41:45.461 --> 41:48.380
Oh, ask Kim Su-jeong. That will do.

41:48.464 --> 41:50.299
I hoped you'd be better than this.

41:51.759 --> 41:53.093
You seriously are the worst.

41:54.470 --> 41:56.639
Attorney Han, watch what you say.

41:59.016 --> 42:00.017
Mr. Shin.

42:01.352 --> 42:05.356
I get that you love money,
but you shouldn't use others.

42:06.732 --> 42:09.527
Those people are already having it hard

42:09.610 --> 42:11.695
even if not for the likes of you.

42:11.779 --> 42:13.113
I'm not like that.

42:13.197 --> 42:15.991
You probably think you have a strong case
now that Ms. Kim came clean.

42:16.784 --> 42:18.077
Dream on.

42:18.160 --> 42:19.787
Su-jeong came clean?

42:22.873 --> 42:25.501
I'll explain it later.

42:27.044 --> 42:28.045
Are you kidding me?

42:28.128 --> 42:29.630
I'm not kidding!

42:32.466 --> 42:36.554
I'm not joking around. I swear.
I'm only trying to reveal the truth.

42:36.637 --> 42:38.889
Can't you just believe me?

42:38.973 --> 42:41.141
What matters to you
is revealing the truth.

42:41.225 --> 42:42.309
That's right.

42:43.143 --> 42:44.770
I will reveal the truth.

42:45.563 --> 42:48.732
So try me with all your might.

42:49.692 --> 42:51.068
I will

42:51.652 --> 42:52.653
crush

42:53.320 --> 42:55.114
all your lies.

43:03.872 --> 43:04.873
What…

43:04.957 --> 43:07.334
She wanted me to prove it,
so I even showed her proof.

43:08.085 --> 43:09.712
Why is she getting worked up?

43:56.842 --> 44:00.095
Check the handwriting
if you can't believe me.

44:00.179 --> 44:01.889
Can't you just believe me?

44:09.355 --> 44:10.898
Hello, Ms. Kim.

44:10.981 --> 44:12.983
Please call Silverwell Laboratory

44:13.067 --> 44:16.153
and ask if I can have access
to Mr. Jeon's office.

44:20.574 --> 44:21.575
Well,

44:23.035 --> 44:25.913
why didn't you tell me
about Su-jeong's confession?

44:26.997 --> 44:28.999
I didn't want you to be heartbroken.

44:30.000 --> 44:33.170
And the credibility of her confession
is in question.

44:33.796 --> 44:36.382
Quite a lot of people
make false confessions in court.

44:37.549 --> 44:38.550
Anything else?

44:39.176 --> 44:42.179
Is there anything else
you couldn't tell me?

44:44.139 --> 44:45.766
No, that's all.

44:46.892 --> 44:48.977
Anyway, aren't we getting there still?

44:49.937 --> 44:51.063
We're almost there.

44:53.482 --> 44:54.483
It's over there.

45:11.291 --> 45:12.292
Come in.

45:16.463 --> 45:19.216
I've contacted the laboratory.
They say you can visit them anytime.

45:19.299 --> 45:20.509
That's good.

45:21.301 --> 45:23.345
This is the number
of a researcher named Gu Hyo-jung.

45:23.429 --> 45:25.264
He wants you to call him when you arrive.

45:25.347 --> 45:26.557
Okay, thank you.

45:28.058 --> 45:30.602
YOU CAN VISIT THE LAB ANYTIME
PLEASE CALL ME BEFORE YOU ARRIVE

45:36.859 --> 45:40.070
It's too big.
I doubt we can find the body.

45:41.196 --> 45:42.990
At least, it's fortunate

45:43.073 --> 45:45.367
that there's only one road
near the potter's field.

45:45.451 --> 45:48.203
And this certainly is
the shortest route to the potter's field.

45:50.080 --> 45:51.582
If I were the culprit,

45:53.083 --> 45:54.918
I'd find somewhere with no CCTV cameras.

45:55.919 --> 45:57.921
Somewhere remote.

45:58.630 --> 46:00.174
CCTV: O
STREETLAMP: O

46:01.008 --> 46:02.759
Somewhere with a side road for cars.

46:04.219 --> 46:05.679
CCTV: X
STREETLAMP: X

46:05.762 --> 46:07.139
Just like that.

46:30.913 --> 46:34.333
The culprit must've taken the body
out of the trunk.

46:48.555 --> 46:52.267
If he dragged the body,
the weeds must've been crushed.

47:01.985 --> 47:03.278
It may have left traces.

47:11.578 --> 47:12.579
I found it.

47:38.897 --> 47:40.274
Gu Hyo-jung speaking.

47:43.944 --> 47:46.780
How many on-site employees are there?

47:48.615 --> 47:51.118
Around 30 researchers.

47:51.743 --> 47:54.997
The management staff and janitors add up

47:55.080 --> 47:56.790
to around ten.

47:57.833 --> 47:59.668
We have a dorm for researchers.

47:59.751 --> 48:02.796
We can't go home often due to work.

48:04.214 --> 48:05.215
I see.

48:06.216 --> 48:07.968
I saw you at the trial this morning.

48:16.184 --> 48:19.605
Yes. I'm a long-time friend of Su-jeong's.

48:21.189 --> 48:25.527
Did you volunteer to be my guide
to tell me something?

48:27.821 --> 48:28.822
Su-jeong

48:29.948 --> 48:31.116
isn't the culprit.

48:36.455 --> 48:38.290
I think it's nearby.

48:46.548 --> 48:48.717
I'll go alone from here.

48:49.301 --> 48:50.969
I don't want you to see.

48:52.095 --> 48:53.555
I'm all right.

48:53.639 --> 48:55.641
It's only an empty shell.

48:56.516 --> 48:57.517
Let's go together.

48:58.769 --> 48:59.770
Okay.

49:11.782 --> 49:12.783
Wait a second.

49:15.285 --> 49:18.413
The color of the soil here is different.
I think it was recently dug up.

49:23.502 --> 49:24.711
Mr. Attorney.

49:25.879 --> 49:28.757
I wonder how Su-jeong moved me
all the way here.

49:28.840 --> 49:31.426
Wait. There's something here.

49:34.054 --> 49:36.431
I was slim, but I weighed 70 kg.

49:37.057 --> 49:42.396
She transferred me in and out of the car,
moved me, and buried me alone?

49:43.438 --> 49:44.648
It makes no sense.

49:47.943 --> 49:49.111
Maybe

49:49.695 --> 49:51.196
she wasn't alone.

49:53.865 --> 49:55.200
If not…

50:01.581 --> 50:06.837
It actually was the Chief's plan
that Sang-ho was to become his son-in-law.

50:06.920 --> 50:08.839
SCIENTIST OF THE YEAR
AWARD CEREMONY

50:15.303 --> 50:16.304
Thank you.

50:16.388 --> 50:20.350
<i>Sang-ho had the best research outcomes,</i>
<i>and the Chief used him to save his wife.</i>

50:20.434 --> 50:22.561
Thank you for considering…

50:23.186 --> 50:24.771
Why didn't I think of it before?

50:27.190 --> 50:30.152
Su-jeong has an accomplice.

50:35.407 --> 50:36.867
Were you aware?

50:39.369 --> 50:42.497
That's not certain yet.

50:43.331 --> 50:44.958
Is that why the trial was held today?

50:45.584 --> 50:46.918
What did Su-jeong say?

50:47.002 --> 50:48.670
You said she confessed.

50:48.754 --> 50:50.172
Did she admit to an accomplice?

50:55.302 --> 50:57.637
Did she admit
to having an accomplice or not?

50:57.721 --> 50:58.764
No.

50:59.765 --> 51:01.933
-She said she killed you alone.
-Why…

51:03.393 --> 51:06.146
Anyone could see that
she has an accomplice, so why…

51:11.777 --> 51:12.778
To protect them.

51:39.930 --> 51:41.264
It was my father-in-law.

51:46.520 --> 51:48.647
Kim Su-jeong refused your visitation.

52:01.326 --> 52:04.621
The truth is, his wife…

52:04.704 --> 52:07.958
Su-jeong's mother is dying
from a rare disease called Concello.

52:09.209 --> 52:10.752
-Then…
-Yes.

52:10.836 --> 52:15.257
Sang-ho was working on a cure
until he suddenly called it quits.

52:15.340 --> 52:16.883
That must've caused it all.

52:16.967 --> 52:19.052
And Su-jeong took the blame.

52:20.053 --> 52:21.638
What are you talking about?

52:22.931 --> 52:25.267
Ms. Kim took the blame for whom?

52:25.350 --> 52:26.977
Isn't it obvious?

52:28.603 --> 52:29.604
The Chief.

52:30.772 --> 52:34.192
Are you saying
Chief Kim Tae-jun is the culprit?

52:35.151 --> 52:37.946
And Ms. Kim confessed for her dad's sake?

52:47.289 --> 52:48.874
<i>No, not for her dad.</i>

52:48.957 --> 52:50.041
<i>For her mom.</i>

52:53.420 --> 52:57.090
Her mother's disease is
paralyzing and atrophying her muscles

52:57.173 --> 52:59.342
as well as destroying her brain cells.

52:59.426 --> 53:01.094
Mom, it's time to eat.

53:03.763 --> 53:06.182
It's me, Su-jeong.

53:09.436 --> 53:11.813
Honey.

53:11.897 --> 53:14.065
-<i>She doesn't recognize anyone…</i>
-I'm right here.

53:14.608 --> 53:16.526
<i>…except her husband, Chief Kim.</i>

53:17.527 --> 53:20.947
<i>When all the evidence pointed to him,</i>
<i>that foolish girl…</i>

53:21.031 --> 53:24.784
…the culprit is around 180 to 185 cm tall…

53:24.868 --> 53:28.997
…the act was done
with a quick and powerful force.

53:29.581 --> 53:34.753
Thus, I've concluded
that the defendant has an accomplice.

53:34.836 --> 53:40.216
I bet Su-jeong couldn't afford
to suspect her dad of killing her husband.

53:40.759 --> 53:45.388
All she had in mind was her mom
who couldn't live without her dad.

53:50.685 --> 53:51.686
I get it now.

53:54.981 --> 53:56.566
That's why she confessed.

54:07.410 --> 54:09.704
Sang-ho, are you okay?

54:10.497 --> 54:11.498
Why…

54:12.874 --> 54:13.875
Why…

54:46.992 --> 54:50.704
Will you be able
to testify the same in court?

54:51.287 --> 54:53.790
Yes, I'll do anything for Su-jeong.

54:55.417 --> 54:57.252
This is Sang-ho's office.

54:57.836 --> 54:59.629
I got the temporary passcode.

54:59.713 --> 55:01.006
LAB DIRECTOR: JEON SANG-HO

55:23.319 --> 55:26.740
Look. Sang-ho wrote this
when he possessed me.

55:48.720 --> 55:50.555
-Bong-su.
-Yes?

55:50.638 --> 55:51.848
Where is I-rang?

55:52.432 --> 55:55.268
He's probably in his office with Sang-ho.

55:55.351 --> 55:56.644
He wouldn't answer his phone.

55:56.728 --> 55:58.813
Oh, really?

56:04.819 --> 56:06.654
He texted me.

56:07.655 --> 56:11.201
<i>Bong-su, I've found out</i>
<i>where Sang-ho's body is buried.</i>

56:11.284 --> 56:14.496
<i>I'm on my way to find it with him.</i>
<i>Call me if you read this.</i>

56:14.579 --> 56:16.664
-A body?
-Oh.

56:16.748 --> 56:21.044
He said he'd find Sang-ho's body
to catch whoever killed him.

56:21.127 --> 56:22.253
That must be why.

56:22.337 --> 56:24.339
Alone with the ghost?

56:24.422 --> 56:25.757
Hello, Father.

56:25.840 --> 56:28.426
Yes, I think so. Why do you ask?

56:29.552 --> 56:32.680
He would go ballistic
at the sight of his own dead body.

56:32.764 --> 56:35.934
His rage will be on another level
from that of previous ghosts.

56:41.356 --> 56:44.275
M-Mother, where are you going?

57:49.048 --> 57:51.384
It certainly is Mr. Jeon's handwriting.

57:53.261 --> 57:55.472
I-rang!

57:56.222 --> 57:57.432
Attorney Han?

57:58.308 --> 58:00.894
Attorney Han, have you seen I-rang?

58:01.436 --> 58:03.188
No, I haven't.

58:03.855 --> 58:05.899
Father, where do you think he is?

58:06.483 --> 58:08.151
If he really is possessed,

58:09.027 --> 58:11.279
it would be a place
where Mr. Jeon would go out of rage.

58:11.863 --> 58:13.823
Mr. Jeon is dead.

58:14.574 --> 58:17.410
She might know.
Jeon Sang-ho's wife is her client.

58:17.494 --> 58:18.620
Tell me.

58:18.703 --> 58:21.748
Where would he go if he were alive?

58:21.831 --> 58:24.501
-So, it's--
-No.

58:24.584 --> 58:28.796
Just imagine.
Let's say Mr. Jeon came back to life.

58:28.880 --> 58:31.049
Where would he be at the moment?

58:31.132 --> 58:33.760
Wouldn't he have gone
to the person who killed him?

58:34.469 --> 58:35.470
To take revenge.

58:35.553 --> 58:37.388
Then, he must've gone to Kim Su-jeong.

58:37.472 --> 58:38.473
No.

58:39.390 --> 58:40.850
He must've gone to Kim Tae-jun.

58:45.688 --> 58:47.732
Ms. Attorney,

58:48.566 --> 58:50.109
I need your help.

59:45.665 --> 59:46.666
Who are you?

59:53.339 --> 59:54.340
Don't come any closer.

59:55.883 --> 59:56.884
Stay back.

59:57.552 --> 59:58.595
Why'd you do it?

59:59.178 --> 01:00:00.430
What are you talking about?

01:00:00.513 --> 01:00:01.598
Do what?

01:00:01.681 --> 01:00:02.932
Why did you kill me?

01:00:04.684 --> 01:00:06.144
W-Who are you?

01:00:06.227 --> 01:00:08.229
Did you kill me
because I dropped the research?

01:00:09.606 --> 01:00:11.649
Did you get rid of me
because I was no longer of use?

01:00:11.733 --> 01:00:13.818
-What are you saying?
-Never mind me.

01:00:14.819 --> 01:00:16.070
How could you…

01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:19.782
How could you do that
to Su-jeong and U-ju?

01:00:20.575 --> 01:00:22.619
Su-jeong is locked up
in a cold prison cell.

01:00:24.203 --> 01:00:25.663
My poor son…

01:00:26.831 --> 01:00:29.250
My son has lost both his parents.

01:00:30.209 --> 01:00:31.794
Do you care only about your wife?

01:00:31.878 --> 01:00:33.296
Who are you?

01:00:33.379 --> 01:00:35.131
Grandpa.

01:00:36.799 --> 01:00:38.134
Grandpa,

01:00:38.217 --> 01:00:40.637
I want to pee.

01:00:40.720 --> 01:00:42.180
-U-ju!
-U-ju.

01:00:42.263 --> 01:00:43.264
U-ju, stay back.

01:00:47.101 --> 01:00:48.311
Please show mercy.

01:00:48.394 --> 01:00:50.605
I'll give you anything you want,
so don't harm him.

01:00:50.688 --> 01:00:51.814
Don't touch my U-ju.

01:00:51.898 --> 01:00:52.982
Please show mercy!

01:00:53.066 --> 01:00:54.108
Give me back my U-ju.

01:00:55.360 --> 01:00:56.944
Give me my son!

01:01:06.913 --> 01:01:07.914
Give me U-ju.

01:01:08.831 --> 01:01:10.458
Give me my son!

01:01:15.129 --> 01:01:16.130
Give him to me.

01:01:16.673 --> 01:01:18.716
Give me back my son!

01:01:23.179 --> 01:01:25.723
I-rang!

01:01:25.807 --> 01:01:28.017
I-rang, stop.

01:01:28.559 --> 01:01:29.727
No.

01:01:30.311 --> 01:01:32.271
Get off me!

01:01:49.330 --> 01:01:50.331
I-rang.

01:01:52.417 --> 01:01:53.751
Are you back in control?

01:01:53.835 --> 01:01:54.961
Mom.

01:01:57.171 --> 01:01:58.172
Where…

01:02:03.177 --> 01:02:04.262
What…

01:02:05.096 --> 01:02:08.266
What have I done?

01:02:09.809 --> 01:02:10.977
It's okay now.

01:02:15.106 --> 01:02:16.899
Everything's okay now.

01:02:16.983 --> 01:02:18.025
It's all right.

01:02:39.839 --> 01:02:42.049
I'm Prosecutor Kim Hyeon-u
from the Seocho Branch Office.

01:02:42.550 --> 01:02:44.051
Mr. Shin I-rang, you're under arrest

01:02:44.135 --> 01:02:47.346
on suspicion of murdering Jeon Sang-ho
and abandoning his body.

01:02:47.430 --> 01:02:50.516
You have the right to an attorney
and the right to remain silent.

01:02:50.600 --> 01:02:52.351
M-Murder?

01:02:52.935 --> 01:02:55.563
-Arrest him.
-No, wait.

01:02:56.147 --> 01:02:58.316
My son killed whom?

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:00.902
We found Jeon Sang-ho's body,

01:03:00.985 --> 01:03:04.489
and his fingerprints were found
on the gloves that were dropped nearby.

01:03:07.074 --> 01:03:08.201
It's a misunderstanding.

01:03:08.993 --> 01:03:10.119
You're mistaken.

01:03:10.203 --> 01:03:11.245
I can explain it all.

01:03:12.079 --> 01:03:14.081
No, please wait.

01:03:14.165 --> 01:03:16.751
-Hold on.
-Please, what in the world…

01:03:16.834 --> 01:03:18.669
-It's not me.
-Mother.

01:03:18.753 --> 01:03:20.463
-Let go of me. I didn't do it!
-I-rang!

01:03:46.364 --> 01:03:48.324
<i>Why did my son-in-law's attorney</i>
<i>come here?</i>

01:03:48.407 --> 01:03:51.494
Did you think
the culprit was your father-in-law?

01:03:51.577 --> 01:03:54.205
-<i>Then, why did you turn yourself in?</i>
-<i>Mom will die without Dad.</i>

01:03:55.206 --> 01:03:57.166
I'm only saying it
because there has been no progress!

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.961
You must've hated him enough to kill him,
Mr. Kim Tae-jun.

01:04:00.044 --> 01:04:02.088
<i>I'll find the real culprit.</i>
<i>If that's Kim Tae-jun,</i>

01:04:02.171 --> 01:04:03.297
I'll put him behind bars.

01:04:03.381 --> 01:04:05.216
<i>With his farsightedness</i>
<i>and fogged-up glasses,</i>

01:04:05.299 --> 01:04:06.884
<i>he must've had to attack several times.</i>

01:04:06.968 --> 01:04:08.219
Your father killed me.

01:04:08.302 --> 01:04:09.595
<i>How could you do that to me?</i>

01:04:09.679 --> 01:04:11.848
How could you possibly do that to me?

01:04:11.931 --> 01:04:16.936
Subtitle translation by:
Eunjin Erica Kim
